Selected Answer: B
For first question vnet to vnet you'd need to peer rather than service endpoint, see;

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-network/tutorial-connect-virtual-networks-portal

For 2, Azure AD can't be used as service endpoint natively, see;

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-network/virtual-network-service-endpoints-overview

"The Microsoft.AzureActiveDirectory tag listed under services supporting service endpoints is used only for supporting service endpoints to ADLS Gen 1. Azure AD doesn't support service endpoints natively."

So vnet to storage is a valid service endpoint, see;

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-network/virtual-network-service-endpoints-overview

And as far as I can find at the moment, 1 service endpoint for storage so 2 required, see;

https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/virtual-network/virtual-network-service-endpoint-policies-portal

